Description: Body sherd of Corinthian black-figured pottery closed vessel, possibly an amphora or oinochoe; exterior: black-figure animal frieze (part of legs and lower body of bird or siren remaining); below, black band; incised inscription on exterior.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 454)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GB.001) (Phase 1)
